---
description: Generate a commit message after code changes
alwaysApply: true
---

After completing any code-editing task, include a "Suggested commit message" section.

The commit message should:
- Be based only on the actual diff made in this task.
- Use Conventional Commits format when possible:
  - feat: for new user-facing functionality
  - fix: for bug fixes
  - refactor: for internal restructuring without behavior change
  - chore: for tooling, config, dependencies, or maintenance
  - docs: for documentation-only changes
  - test: for tests
  - perf: for performance improvements
- Be concise but specific.
- Prefer one-line commit messages unless the change is large enough to need a body.
- Do not create the git commit unless explicitly asked.